Negotiator					KEY:Bard Archetype ~ Negotiator									CATEGORY:Archetype		TYPE:Archetype.BardArchetype.BardBardicKnowledge.BardCountersong.BardInspireCourage.BardInspireGreatness.BardVersatilePerformance.BardLoreMaster														PRECLASS:1,Bard=1		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Archetype,Bard Archetype ~ Negotiator],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Archetype,TYPE.BardBardicKnowledge,TYPE.BardCountersong,TYPE.BardInspireCourage,TYPE.BardInspireGreatness,TYPE.BardVersatilePerformance,TYPE.BardLoreMaster]																			DESC:Bards are experts at manipulating the emotions and perceptions of others. Negotiators are those bards who take the skills of a performer and apply them to the realms of business and law.																																																																																																																		ABILITY:Bard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Negotiator ~ Hard Bargainer|PRECLASS:1,Bard=1	ABILITY:Bard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Negotiator ~ Counterargument|PRECLASS:1,Bard=1	ABILITY:Bard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Negotiator ~ Fast Talk|PRECLASS:1,Bard=1	ABILITY:Bard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Negotiator ~ Binding Contract|PRECLASS:1,Bard=9	ABILITY:Bard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Negotiator ~ Rogue Talents|PRECLASS:1,Bard=2	ABILITY:Bard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Negotiator ~ Master of Rhetoric|PRECLASS:1,Bard=5																																																																																																																																																																																								COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.18	ASPECT:Archetype Base Class|Bard
Hard Bargainer				KEY:Negotiator ~ Hard Bargainer									CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.BardClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.BardBardicKnowledge																																																																																									DESC:A negotiator adds half his class level (minimum 1) on Bluff, Diplomacy, Intimidate, Knowledge (local), and Sense Motive checks. This ability replaces bardic knowledge.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																			BONUS:SKILL|Bluff,Intimidate,Knowledge (Local),Sense Motive|ceil(BardLVL/2)																																																																																																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.18
Counterargument				KEY:Negotiator ~ Counterargument									CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.BardClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Supernatural.BardCountersong																																																																																										DESC:This performance acts as countersong, except a negotiator can use only Perform (act, comedy, oratory, or sing) to perform a counterargument.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.18
Fast Talk					KEY:Negotiator ~ Fast Talk										CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.BardClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Supernatural.BardInspireCourage																																																																																										DESC:A negotiator can use performance to affect the perceptions of any number of targets that can hear him. While the negotiator performs, these targets take a -1 penalty on saving throws against enchantment (charm) and illusion (figment, glamer, or shadow) effects, as well as a penalty on Appraise checks equal to half the negotiator's level (minimum -1). A target that fails its Appraise check believes that the object in question is worth 10% more or less (negotiator's choice) than its actual value. At 5th, 11th, and 17th levels, the saving throw penalty increases by 1 and the shift in an object's perceived value increases by 10%. Fast talk is a language-dependent, mind-affecting ability that uses audible components. This performance replaces inspire courage.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.18
Binding Contract				KEY:Negotiator ~ Binding Contract									CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.BardClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.SpellLike.BardInspireGreatness																																																																																										DESC:The negotiator can bind another creature's promise to the negotiator with a geas. This acts as lesser geas, except the creature must have Hit Dice equal to or less than the negotiator's level. The target can negate this effect with a successful Will save (DC = 10 + 1/2 the negotiator's level + the negotiator's Charisma modifier). The geas is discharged if the negotiator breaks his end of the bargain. Using this ability requires 3 rounds of continuous performance, and the target must be able to see and hear the bard throughout the performance. At 18th level, this effect acts as geas/quest (no HD limit, and the target cannot attempt a saving throw). Binding contract is an enchantment (compulsion), mind-affecting, language-dependent ability that relies on audible components. This performance replaces inspire greatness.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.19
Rogue Talents				KEY:Negotiator ~ Rogue Talents									CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.BardClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.BardVersatilePerformance																																																																													DEFINE:RogueTalentLVL|0								DESC:A negotiator gains a rogue talent, as the rogue class feature of the same name. At 6th level and every 4 levels thereafter, the negotiator gains an additional rogue talent. A negotiator cannot select a rogue talent that modifies the sneak attack ability. At 10th level and every 4 levels thereafter, a negotiator can select an advanced rogue talent in place of a rogue talent. A negotiator cannot select an advanced talent that modifies the sneak attack ability. This ability replaces versatile performance.																																																																																																																																																															BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Rogue Talent|(RogueTalentLVL+2)/4																																																																																																																																		BONUS:VAR|RogueTalentLVL|BardLVL																												SOURCEPAGE:p.19
Master of Rhetoric			KEY:Negotiator ~ Master of Rhetoric									CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.BardClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.BardLoreMaster																																																																																										DESC:The negotiator can take 10 on any Bluff, Diplomacy, Intimidate, Knowledge (local), or Sense Motive check ifhe has ranks in that skill. A negotiator can choose not to take 10 and can instead roll normally. In addition, the negotiator can take 20 on one of those skill checks (without spending any additional time). The negotiator can do this once per day at 5th level, twice per day at 11th level, and three times per day at 17th level. This ability replaces lore master.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.11

# ==============================
# Domain Powers
# ==============================

Void Form					KEY:Domain Power ~ Void Form										CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural.DomainPower																																																																																																DESC:You can become semi-tangible as a standard action. While in this form, you are immune to critical hits and gain a +1 deflection bonus to AC. This bonus increases by 1 at 8th level and every 4 levels thereafter. You can use this power a number of rounds per day equal to your cleric level. These rounds need not be consecutive.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.16
Noble Visage				KEY:Domain Power ~ Noble Visage									CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural.DomainPower																																																																																																DESC:You gain a +1 bonus on Charisma checks and Charisma-based skill checks against creatures that share your creature type (and subtype, if you are a humanoid). This bonus increases by 1 for every 5 levels you possess. As a standard action, you can touch an ally to grant her your noble visage bonus against creatures that share her creature type (or subtype) for 1 minute. When you use this ability, you lose your noble visage bonus for 1 minute. You can use this ability a number of times per day equal to 3 + your Wisdom modifier.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.16
Go with the Flow				KEY:Domain Power ~ Go with the Flow									CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural.DomainPower																																																																																																DESC:You can touch a creature as a standard action to suppress its strong emotions. The target is affected as the calm emotions spell, except it can still take violent actions and violent actions against the target do not end the effect. This effect lasts a number of rounds equal to 1/2 your cleric level (minimum 1). You can use this ability a number times per day equal to 3 + your Wisdom modifier.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.17
Fool's Privilege				KEY:Domain Power ~ Fool's Privilege									CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural.DomainPower																																																																																																DESC:You can use this power as a swift action when you fail a Bluff, Diplomacy, or Intimidate check outside of combat. You suffer no negative effects due to the failed check, and the next round you can attempt the check again without the usual penalty for a failed attempt. You can use this ability once per day, and one additional time per day for every 4 levels beyond 1st.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.17
Spirit Touch				KEY:Domain Power ~ Spirit Touch									CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural.DomainPower																																																																																																DESC:As a swift action, you can give your natural weapons or any weapons you wield the ghost touch weapon special ability. You can use this power a number of rounds per day equal to your cleric level. These rounds need not be consecutive.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.17
Taboo						KEY:Domain Power ~ Taboo										CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural.DomainPower																																																																																																DESC:When a creature touches you or strikes you with a melee attack, you can activate this power as an immediate action. That creature takes a -1 penalty on saving throws for i minute. This penalty increases by 1 for every 5 levels you possess. When you use this ability, you lose your resistance bonus granted by the Protection domain for i minute. You can use this ability a number of times per day equal to 3 + your Wisdom modifier.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.17

